Vim cheatsheet for custom keybindings

leader = <space>

CTRL+w+v - split window vertically
CTRL+w+s - split window horizontally
CTRL+[h,j,k,l] - move to window in direction

leader+p - invoke fzf

leader+A - search the codebase for the word under cursor
leader+a - enter string to be searched in codebase
leader+c - toggle open/close the CtrlSF window
p - preview file in CtrlSF window

leader+cc - comment lines (use visual mode to comment multiple lines)
leader+cu - uncomment lines (use visual mode to uncomment multiple lines)

zc - close fold
zo - open fold
